Kidnapped Japanese businessmanNobuyuki Wakaoji has been released after four months incaptivity, Presidential spokesman Teodoro Benigno said.    Benigno told reporters the 53-year-old Mitsui and Co Ltdexecutive was freed yesterday and is being held in anundisclosed hospital.    He gave no further details on the release, which wasconfirmed minutes earlier by a Mitsui spokesman in Tokyo. Reuter&#3;